    <p> I spent the last 2.5 days in Auckland. It was planned to fight against the very likely jet during this time. So that I was able to sleep quite well on the flights and found the new day / night rhythm (11 hours later than in Germany), I had no major problems. Only on the first day after arrival I had a little follower in the afternoon. But sometimes I also have them at home. Usually after a hearty and big noon. </p>
    <p> On Thursday, the day of my journey, I reached the Pentlands Backpacker Hostel around 4 p.m. Unfortunately the reception was still closed but after a few seconds a friendly gentleman came and let me check in. He gave me the key and showed me my bed for the 3 nights. I was lucky again and got a single bed in a 5 bed room and it even stood by the window. I left my bags in the room and started looking for Sam. As discussed by SMS before, I found her outside in the meadow next to the accommodation. </p>
    <p> After a few minutes of chatting, we decided to move a little and climb Mount Eden with its almost 200 meters. From up there we had a really nice view of the city. Since Mount Eden is a volcano, you could see the crater very well with its about 50m diameter. But this was already fully overgrown with lawn. </p>
  </div>
