    <p> After we were around a round and the wind up there was very cold, we decided to go to the nearby food market and to shop for me for the first few days. When I saw the prices, I fell almost in the back. A single pepper or a bag of Haribo costs $ 3 (2 &euro;) in Auckland. A medium glass Nutella costs $ 9 (6 &euro;). Sam and I decided that we will descend our additives here and try without getting along. But there are also cheaper foods. Bananas, Kiwis, some varieties sausage and cheese can be obtained here for a good course. After shopping, we went back to the hostel, cooked and enjoyed the rest of the day. </p>
    <p> On Friday I made my way to the city. Since the weather was good, I went on foot to really see the new environment. My goal was the Sky Tower. You could already see it well from a long time and it made it just to walk there. Once on site, I looked up and saw someone jumped down from above. Fortunately, this person was secured on 3 ropes and gently landed on the planned platform. </p>
