  <div class="col-md-9">
    <p> My plan was now to get the 220m high viewing platform. So off through the entrance and to the cash register. So that I did not have to pay the full price of $ 28, but only the reduced backpacker price of $ 18 I had a confirmation from the hostel. That worked without any problems and I was able to go up on the 220m. From there I took many, hopefully beautiful photos of Auckland, the port in which a Hamburg container ship was extinguishing and of course the surrounding islands. </p>
    <p> I spent several hours on this floor before I slowly turned down again. I stopped again at a height of about 186m and looked around there again in peace and checked the sprinklers past. I made it very different from watching and I decided to go to the fresh air at the foot of the tower. </p>
    <p> In search of an MC Donalds (because of free WiFi and a small snack) I came past a Irish style in whiskey shop in which I quickly tried New Zealand whiskey and found it good. When I arrived at MC Donalds, I rummaged for about a hour on the Internet to things that I would like to do in the next few days. </p>
    <p> Since the weather was increasingly windy and wet, I decided to go back to the hostel and end the evening comfortably on site. </p>
    <p> Saturday is not really worth mentioning because it rained from barrels throughout the morning and storm all day.  I did not go further than up to the property border. I brought the day around the corner with reading, cooking and exchange ideas with other travelers. Most other guests in the hostel are also Germans. </p>
